	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: MMC3 Problem</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">3gengames wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You guys do see the scrolls also change when the IRQ's happen? This is pretty much just an address line problem. I don't see why we're all guessing crap here, it's very obvious.</div><br /><br />HUH?  Scrolls change when IRQ's happen means the address lines are messed up?  If there was anything significantly wrong with the address lines then there would be other glitches.  CHR A12 is clearly toggling just fine based on the ability to fetch back ground tiles and sprites just fine.  <br /><br />Any graphics that rely on IRQs will be trashed without IRQs firing.  Who knows what kind of scrolling effects you'll get without the IRQ working properly.  Not to mention all other games work just fine which don't have cartridge IRQs.<br /><br />Isn't there a pull-up resistor on the IRQ line?  Might be worth checking if you're certain there's continuity from the MMC3 to the CPU on the IRQ line.  I'd bet a large sum of money the issue is IRQ related and not CHR related.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


